title: Strictly Come Dancing: From One Direction to Elvis Costello, here's this week's song and dance list - Strictly Come Dancing Reality TV
text: Strictly Come Dancing is already at week 5 and things are getting serious. Jay McGuiness jived his way to a 10 in week 3, but will we see another this time? Check out the coming weekend's song and dance list and get speculating:1. Ainsley Harriott & Natalie Lowe © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: JiveSong: 'Shake, Rattle and Roll' - Bill Haley and the Comets2. Anita Rani & Gleb Savchenko © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: TangoSong: 'Sweet Disposition' - Temper Trap3. Carol Kirkwood & Pasha Kovalev © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: Viennese WaltzSong: 'I've Been Loving You Too Long' - Seal4. Georgia May Foote & Giovanni Pernice © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: SalsaSong: 'You Make Me Feel (Mighty Real)' - Sylvester5. Helen George & Aljaz Skorjanec © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: QuickstepSong: 'You Can't Hurry Love' - Diana Ross and the Supremes6. Jamelia & Tristan MacManus © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: FoxtrotSong: 'Because You Loved Me' - Celine Dion7. Jay McGuiness & Aliona Vilani © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: Paso DobleSong: 'It's My Life' - Bon Jovi8. Jeremy Vine & Karen Clifton © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: WaltzSong: 'She' - Elvis Costello9. Katie Derham & Anton Du Beke © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: SalsaSong: 'It Had Better Be Tonight' - Michael Buble10. Kellie Bright & Kevin Clifton © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: JiveSong: 'One Way or Another' - One Direction11. Kirsty Gallacher & Brendan Cole © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: Viennese WaltzSong: 'This Year's Love' - David Gray12. Peter Andre & Janette Manrara © BBC / Guy Levy Dance: RumbaSong: 'Thinking Out Loud' - Ed SheeranStrictly Come Dancing continues on Saturday (October 24) at 6.30pm on BBC One.
